title: Systems working properly after first space docking
description: BEIJING， Nov. 3 (Xinhua) -- Equipment and systems have been working properly since the initial joining of the unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 and the space lab module Tiangong-1 at 1:36 a.m. Thursday， China's manned space program spokeswoman Wu Ping said.
cleanContent: BEIJING, Nov. 3 (Xinhua) -- Equipment and systems have been working properly since the initial joining of the unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 and the space lab module Tiangong-1 at 1:36 a.m. Thursday, China's manned space program spokeswoman Wu Ping said.The coupled spacecraft has orbited earth nearly six times since the successful docking, Wu told a press conference here.																																																																								|  |
